    $review$Helen King$review$,    -- reviewer_name
    1,                     -- rating
    NULL,                          -- title
    $review$I cannot recommend Richmond Hill Assisted Living, as my family's experience was heartbreaking; the neglect and lack of care led to multiple ER visits for our loved one, and the disorganization and poor communication made a difficult situation even worse. If you truly care about your loved one, please look elsewhere—this facility is not only overpriced but also fails to provide the basic safety and support that residents need.

---
Additional details: If you truly care about your loved one, don't ever consider this place to take them! Our family member was neglected,  emotionally abused,  lack of care, which caused her to be taken to the ER on 2 separate occasions in less than 6 mths of being here! One for drastic medication change and the 2nd ER visit was for malnutrition! They let her lay in bed, unmonitored and not fed for 5 days and then called to say they were sending her to the ER! They also denied her care from the ER doctors,  until I filed an abuse and neglect complaint with DSS! This place is filthy, never cleaned, broken appliances,  no activities of any kind! Everything stated on their website listings are totally FALSE!! NEVER take your loved ones here!  I wouldn't even give 1 star to this place! Total NEGLECT!$review$,         -- comment
